  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Audit Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>Genuine CA PAC is a public accounting firm providing a comprehensive full range of professional services to our clients based locally and overseas in a variety of industries.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will support audit and tax processes by preparing financial statements, tax computations, and reports while maintaining accurate documentation and ensuring data integrity for corporate compliance.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct audit tasks carefully to verify financial data accuracy and compliance with standards</li><li>Prepare financial statements and XBRL reports to meet regulatory and client requirements</li><li>Calculate corporate tax liabilities accurately for timely tax filing</li><li>Cross-check and reconcile financial information to ensure consistency and correctness</li><li>Organize and maintain proper documentation and filing systems for easy retrieval and audit trails</li><li>Manage confidential information with professionalism and discretion</li><li>Collaborate with team members and work independently to complete assigned tasks efficiently</li><li>Handle multiple tasks simultaneously while maintaining attention to detail</li><li>Perform ad hoc administrative duties as assigned to support team operations</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Positive work attitude and strong sense of responsibility</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Word and Excel to prepare reports and documentation</li></ul>",
